---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Nelson Kwesi — The work that repeats should disappear. What's left is the work that matters."
  description="Nine years writing software. Now building systems and tools that handle the repetition so business owners can focus on what actually matters."
  activeNav="home"
>
  <style>
    /* Hero */
    .hero { padding: 64px 0 56px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); position: relative; }
    .hero::after {
      content: '';
      position: absolute; left: 0; right: 0; top: 28%; height: 2px;
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(240,192,48,0.07) 30%, rgba(240,192,48,0.14) 50%, rgba(240,192,48,0.07) 70%, transparent);
      pointer-events: none;
    }
    .hero-inner { padding: 28px 28px 24px; }
    .sys-line {
      font-size: 0.58rem; color: var(--amber-dim); letter-spacing: 0.14em;
      text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 20px;
      display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;
    }
    .sys-line::before { content: '>'; color: var(--amber); }
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4.5vw, 3.1rem); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.06;
      color: var(--ink); margin-bottom: 20px;
      text-shadow: 0 0 28px rgba(240,192,48,0.12);
    }
    .hero h1 em { font-style: normal; color: var(--amber); text-shadow: 0 0 18px rgba(240,192,48,0.45); }
    .hero-desc { font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--ink-dim); line-height: 1.82; max-width: 560px; margin-bottom: 28px; }
    .hero-links { display: flex; gap: 14px; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; }
    .hero-link-secondary { font-size: 0.65rem; color: var(--amber-dim); letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(240,192,48,0.25); padding-bottom: 1px; }
    .hero-link-secondary:hover { color: var(--amber); border-color: var(--amber); }
    .vhs-stamp { position: absolute; bottom: 14px; right: 18px; font-size: 0.52rem; color: var(--amber-dim); letter-spacing: 0.08em; opacity: 0.55; }

    /* Problems */
    .problem-list { margin-top: 32px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0; }
    .problem-item {
      padding: 22px 20px;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(240,192,48,0.08);
      font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--ink-dim); line-height: 1.5;
      display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: baseline;
    }
    .problem-item:last-of-type { border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(240,192,48,0.08); }
    .problem-item::before { content: '"'; color: var(--amber); font-size: 1.4rem; line-height: 1; flex-shrink: 0; opacity: 0.6; }
    .problem-note {
      margin-top: 36px; font-size: 0.68rem; color: var(--ink-dim); line-height: 1.75;
      max-width: 560px; padding-left: 4px;
    }
    .problem-note strong { color: var(--ink); }

    /* Case studies */
    .case-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1px; background: var(--border); margin-top: 24px; }
    .case-card { background: var(--bg); padding: 32px 28px; }
    .status-badge { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; font-size: 0.52rem; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; margin-bottom: 14px; }
    .status-badge.live { color: var(--amber); }
    .status-badge.live::before { content: '●'; animation: blink 1.4s step-end infinite; color: var(--amber); }
    .status-badge.done { color: rgba(100,230,100,0.85); }
    .status-badge.done::before { content: '■'; color: rgba(100,230,100,0.85); }
    .case-section-heading { font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3.5vw, 2.4rem) !important; font-weight: 700; color: var(--ink); margin-bottom: 10px; line-height: 1.1; }
    .case-card h3 { font-size: 0.92rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--ink); margin-bottom: 8px; line-height: 1.2; }
    .case-card p { font-size: 0.63rem; color: var(--ink-dim); line-height: 1.72; margin-bottom: 14px; }
    .case-items-label { font-size: 0.5rem; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--amber-dim); margin-bottom: 6px; }
    .case-items { list-style: none; }
    .case-items li { font-size: 0.6rem; color: var(--ink-dim); padding: 4px 0; border-top: 1px solid rgba(240,192,48,0.07); display: flex; gap: 8px; }
    .case-items li::before { content: '>'; color: var(--amber); flex-shrink: 0; }

    /* Audit nudge — soft, not dominant */
    .audit-nudge {
      margin-top: 32px;
      padding: 28px;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
      display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; gap: 24px; flex-wrap: wrap;
    }
    .audit-nudge p { font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--ink-dim); line-height: 1.7; max-width: 480px; margin: 0; }
    .audit-nudge p strong { color: var(--ink); }

    /* Terminal panel */
    .hero-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 0;
      align-items: center;
    }
    .hero-left { padding: 28px 28px 24px; }
    .terminal-panel {
      border-left: 1px solid var(--border);
      padding: 28px 24px;
      height: 100%;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      justify-content: center;
      background: rgba(240,192,48,0.015);
    }
    .term-bar {
      display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;
      margin-bottom: 20px; padding-bottom: 12px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(240,192,48,0.1);
    }
    .term-dot { width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--amber); opacity: 0.4; }
    .term-dot.on { opacity: 1; animation: blink 1.4s step-end infinite; }
    .term-title { font-size: 0.44rem; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--amber-dim); }
    .term-body { font-family: var(--font); font-size: 0.62rem; line-height: 2; }
    .term-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0; overflow: hidden; }
    .term-label { color: var(--ink-faint); flex-shrink: 0; min-width: 0; }
    .term-label span { color: rgba(240,192,48,0.45); margin-right: 6px; }
    .term-dots { flex: 1; color: rgba(240,192,48,0.12); letter-spacing: 0.06em; overflow: hidden; white-space: nowrap; }
    .term-status {
      font-size: 0.5rem; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase;
      flex-shrink: 0; margin-left: 8px; opacity: 0;
      transition: opacity 0.3s ease;
    }
    .term-status.done { color: rgba(100,220,100,0.85); opacity: 1; }
    .term-status.processing { color: var(--amber); opacity: 1; }
    .term-divider { border: none; border-top: 1px solid rgba(240,192,48,0.07); margin: 10px 0; }
    .term-output {
      font-size: 0.6rem; color: var(--amber); letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      opacity: 0; transition: opacity 0.5s ease;
      margin-top: 2px;
    }
    .term-output.visible { opacity: 1; }
    .term-cursor { display: inline-block; width: 7px; height: 0.65em; background: var(--amber); vertical-align: middle; animation: blink 1s step-end infinite; margin-left: 3px; }

    /* About teaser */
    .about-inner { max-width: 600px; }
    .about-inner p { font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--ink-dim); line-height: 1.85; margin-bottom: 18px; }
    .about-inner p:last-of-type { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .about-inner .socials { margin-top: 24px; }

    @media (max-width: 700px) {
      .hero-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .terminal-panel { border-left: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
      .case-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
      .audit-nudge { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
    }
  </style>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="box">
      <span class="box-label">INIT //</span>
      <div class="hero-grid">

        <!-- Left: copy -->
        <div class="hero-left">
          <p class="sys-line">Software Engineer &middot; Builder &middot; Building in Public</p>
          <h1>The work that repeats<br/>should <em>disappear.</em></h1>
          <p class="hero-desc">
            What's left is the work that matters.<br/>
            Nine years writing software. Now building systems and tools that handle
            the repetition, so the people running them can finally think about the business again.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-links">
            <a class="btn" href="https://youtube.com/@nelsonkwesi" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Follow the Builds</a>
            <a class="hero-link-secondary" href="/about">About Nelson &rarr;</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Right: retro terminal -->
        <div class="terminal-panel">
          <div class="term-bar">
            <div class="term-dot on"></div>
            <div class="term-dot"></div>
            <div class="term-dot"></div>
            <span class="term-title">repetition.exe &nbsp;// running</span>
          </div>
          <div class="term-body" id="term-body">
            <div class="term-row" id="row-0">
              <span class="term-label"><span>&gt;</span>follow-up emails</span>
              <span class="term-dots">&nbsp;......................&nbsp;</span>
              <span class="term-status" id="st-0">HANDLED</span>
            </div>
            <div class="term-row" id="row-1">
              <span class="term-label"><span>&gt;</span>booking confirmations</span>
              <span class="term-dots">&nbsp;................&nbsp;</span>
              <span class="term-status" id="st-1">HANDLED</span>
            </div>
            <div class="term-row" id="row-2">
              <span class="term-label"><span>&gt;</span>review responses</span>
              <span class="term-dots">&nbsp;...................&nbsp;</span>
              <span class="term-status" id="st-2">HANDLED</span>
            </div>
            <div class="term-row" id="row-3">
              <span class="term-label"><span>&gt;</span>missed call callbacks</span>
              <span class="term-dots">&nbsp;...............&nbsp;</span>
              <span class="term-status" id="st-3">HANDLED</span>
            </div>
            <div class="term-row" id="row-4">
              <span class="term-label"><span>&gt;</span>daily admin reports</span>
              <span class="term-dots">&nbsp;.................&nbsp;</span>
              <span class="term-status" id="st-4">HANDLED</span>
            </div>
            <hr class="term-divider"/>
            <div class="term-output" id="term-output">
              &gt; your team is free to think<span class="term-cursor"></span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
      <span class="vhs-stamp">CH:01 &nbsp;&#9654; PLAY</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    (function () {
      const statuses = [0,1,2,3,4].map(i => document.getElementById('st-' + i));
      const output   = document.getElementById('term-output');
      const DELAY    = 520;

      function reset() {
        statuses.forEach(s => { s.className = 'term-status processing'; s.textContent = '...'; });
        output.classList.remove('visible');
      }

      function run() {
        reset();
        statuses.forEach((s, i) => {
          setTimeout(() => {
            s.textContent = 'HANDLED';
            s.className = 'term-status done';
            if (i === statuses.length - 1) {
              setTimeout(() => { output.classList.add('visible'); }, 400);
              setTimeout(run, 3200);
            }
          }, (i + 1) * DELAY);
        });
      }

      run();
    })();
  </script>

  <!-- The Problems -->
  <div class="section">
    <p class="sec-label">WHY THIS EXISTS // THE PROBLEMS</p>
    <h2>What business owners actually say.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">Not "I want AI." Not "I want automation." This:</p>
    <div class="problem-list">
      <div class="problem-item">I just want to stop doing the same thing over and over every day.</div>
      <div class="problem-item">I want to know when a customer is about to leave before they leave.</div>
      <div class="problem-item">I want someone to handle the follow-ups because we forget and lose deals.</div>
      <div class="problem-item">I want my team to stop spending half their day on admin.</div>
    </div>
    <p class="problem-note">
      Nobody said "I want an AI agent." Nobody mentioned a tech stack.
      They described frustrations. They described time they want back.
      <strong>That's what we build for.</strong> The tech is just the means. The problem is the point.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Case Studies -->
  <div class="section">
    <p class="sec-label">CASE STUDIES // BUSINESSES WE HAVE AUTOMATED</p>
    <h2 class="case-section-heading">What it looks like when ops stop being someone's job.</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">Two examples. Here is what stopped being manual.</p>
    <div class="case-grid">
      <div class="case-card">
        <span class="status-badge live">PROPERTY MANAGEMENT</span>
        <h3>The Rental That<br/>Runs Overnight</h3>
        <p>Guests message at midnight. Cleaners need scheduling. Reviews pile up. A system now handles all of it without anyone on call. Human oversight stays. The daily ops take care of themselves.</p>
        <p class="case-items-label">WHAT STOPPED BEING MANUAL</p>
        <ul class="case-items">
          <li>Guest and tenant messages answered 24/7, check-ins included</li>
          <li>Cleaners and contractors hired automatically via Thumbtack and Angi</li>
          <li>Maintenance requests routed to the right person without a call</li>
          <li>Review responses written and posted without anyone touching them</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="case-card">
        <span class="status-badge done">CONTENT BUSINESS</span>
        <h3>One Topic In.<br/>A Week of Content Out.</h3>
        <p>One topic goes in. Scripts, lead magnets, and posts come out for every platform. Nobody staring at a blank page. What used to take a team a week now runs in an hour.</p>
        <p class="case-items-label">WHAT STOPPED BEING MANUAL</p>
        <ul class="case-items">
          <li>Finding what the audience actually complains about, pulled fresh every 30 days</li>
          <li>Scripts with 3 hook variations so the best one gets filmed</li>
          <li>PDF lead magnets generated from the best-performing scripts</li>
          <li>Full pipeline from idea to posted, nothing tracked by hand</li>
          <li>Top performers auto-saved to an inspiration library for future use</li>
          <li>Blog, carousel, and repurposed formats output in the same run</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- What else can be automated -->
    <div class="problem-note" style="margin-top:28px; padding: 20px; border: 1px solid rgba(240,192,48,0.1);">
      <strong>These are two examples. There are thousands more.</strong> Follow-up sequences that never get sent. Quotes that take three days to go out. Leads that fall through because nobody remembered to call back. Invoices chased manually every month. Onboarding docs emailed one by one. Appointment reminders that depend on someone remembering.
      <br/><br/>
      Whatever your team keeps doing every week because there is no system for it yet, that is exactly what we build.
    </div>

    <!-- Soft audit nudge -->
    <div class="audit-nudge">
      <p>
        <strong>Want to see what this looks like in your business?</strong> One session.
        We find the biggest time drain and build the fix while you watch.
        30 minutes. $500. You leave with something working.
      </p>
      <a class="btn" href="/ai-audit">Book a Session &rarr;</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- About Teaser -->
  <div class="section">
    <p class="sec-label">// ABOUT</p>
    <div class="about-inner">
      <p>Born in Ghana. Moved to the US for college. Spent close to a decade building software: JavaScript, TypeScript, backend systems, banking platforms.</p>
      <p>Then got serious about what these tools could actually do in production. Not prototypes. Real systems running real businesses. Started building two of them and documenting everything publicly.</p>
      <p>Steve Jobs didn&apos;t just build the thing. He made people understand why it mattered. That&apos;s the idea here. We build, we share, we figure it out together.</p>
      <div class="socials">
        <a class="social" href="https://x.com/nelsonkwesix" target="_blank" rel="noopener">X: @nelsonkwesix</a>
        <a class="social" href="https://youtube.com/@nelsonkwesi" target="_blank" rel="noopener">YouTube: Nelson Kwesi</a>
        <a class="social" href="https://instagram.com/nelsonkwesi.xyz" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Instagram: @nelsonkwesi.xyz</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</SiteLayout>
